# Mechanics Module V5 — Implementation Plan

Next-generation mechanics evaluation adding stride length/direction, arm positioning/timing, and a new "most loaded" checkpoint with full loading profile — all from 2D open-side video.

## Design Decisions Summary

| Decision | Answer |
|---|---|
| 3D vs 2D | **2D only** — no 3D tech |
| Distance calibration | **Player height** from [roster.json](file:///Users/traftonobrien/Desktop/pitch-tracker/web/data/roster.json) |
| Stride output | Feet/inches + % body height + direction angle |
| Foot strike definition | **Full foot plant** — both heel AND toe grounded |
| "Weight bearing" | New sub-phase: weight fully transferred to lead leg (after FS) |
| Arm alignment view | 2D open-side projection (with confidence caveat) |
| Elbow flexion | Shoulder→elbow→wrist angle at weight bearing |
| Arm flip timing | 45-90° external rotation, scored 0-10 vs weight bearing |
| "Most loaded" | Composite: lead knee lowest + maximum hip hinge, between PLL and FS |
| Pelvis/loading | Full profile: hip hinge + hip-to-knee + trunk lean |
| Counter rotation | Shoulder rotation from SET baseline + hip-shoulder sep |
| COM estimation | Simple proxy (hip+shoulder midpoint), upgrade later |
| Drift thresholds | General baseball biomechanics guidelines |
| Efficiency score | Add all new metrics immediately as official |
| Coach pack | 5th "most loaded" panel + annotations on existing panels |
| Web display | Backend only — no web changes this iteration |

